Class Customer

java.lang.Object
com.example.protrack.customer.Customer
public class Customer extends Object
The Customer class represents a customer. The Customer class contains details about the customer.

  • Constructor Details

    • Customer

      public Customer(Integer customerId, String firstName, String lastName, String email, String phoneNumber, String billingAddress, String shippingAddress, String status)
      Constructs a new Customer object with the bellow parameters.
      Parameters:
      customerId - the unique ID of the customer, must not be null or negative
      firstName - the first name of the customer, must not be null
      lastName - the last name of the customer, must not be null
      email - the email address of the customer, must not be null and must contain '@' and '.'
      phoneNumber - the phone number of the customer, can be null, but must be exactly 10 digits if provided
      billingAddress - the billing address of the customer
      shippingAddress - the shipping address of the customer
      status - the status of the customer, must be either "Active" or "Inactive"
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if any mandatory field is null, email is invalid, or status is incorrect
